festival.introText:
Junction 2 2023. A year of rebirth, regrowth and new collaborations.

Returning to their original home, the inimitable Boston Manor Park, this year’s edition is set to be the boldest Junction 2 yet, as they gather our energy from recent years to present a collective experience to live long in the memory.

Having confirmed a host of familiar favourites alongside new members of the Junction 2 family, the first names for the 2023 edition will be revealed on January 10th, at 12pm. This year also sees a renewed focus on alliances, with 23 DJs delivering spellbinding back to back sets. The pairings have all been chosen to allow the artists to fully express themselves, creating a truly unique experience, both in the booth and on the dancefloor.

Overall, this is Junction 2’s most forward-thinking and varied line-up yet, perfectly suited to today’s open-minded and ever-changing scene. Returning to home soil once again, this really feels like it’s going to be something special – join them for an unparalleled two day celebration of underground sonics and the very best electronic music the scene has to offer.

reviews.body: Great venue, music was decent. Bit hard to get to the front under the bridge. Maybe open another exit closer to the front if poss. Well organised, crowd happy and well behaved

reviews.title: Review of Junction 2

faqs.question: When is Junction 2?
faqs.answer: Junction 2 returns to Boston Manor Park Friday July 21st and Saturday July 22nd 2023.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: How do I get to Junction 2?
faqs.answer:
By Car - Public transport is recommended to travel to Junction 2 as there is limited parking. 

By Rail - Hadley Wood station or Oakleigh Park station are the nearest train stations to Trent Country Park.

By Tube - The closest tube station with a 5 minute walk to the festival site is Cockfosters Tube Station.

faqs.question: Where is Junction 2?
faqs.answer: Junction 2 is located in Boston Manor Park in London. Postcode TW8 9JX.

faqs.question: Do I need to print my ticket?
faqs.answer: No, you can access your ticket(s) at any time in your order history or the 'my tickets' section of the Skiddle app.

faqs.question: Does Junction 2 have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: No, Junction 2 is a non-camping festival so camping equipment is not needed, however, there is plenty of alternative accommodation to choose from.

faqs.question: Does Junction 2 have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: Yes, you must be 18 or over to attend Junction 2 Festival. You may be asked to show photo ID.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into Junction 2?
faqs.answer: You are not allowed to bring your own food and drink into Junction 2. There will be a wide variety of food and drink stalls inside the festival, serving up organic, vegetarian and vegan options.

faqs.question: What are the set times?
faqs.answer: The set times are generally released on the first day of the festival.
